interests: understanding the role of AI Engineer

key_facts: AI Engineers are responsible for transforming AI models from ideas to practical systems
They work with algorithms, data, infrastructure, performance, and user interaction
Not all AI Engineers do deep learning; they choose algorithms based on problem, data, and system requirements

AI Engineers start projects by understanding the business or product problem, then identifying necessary data, evaluating data quality, proposing a modeling approach, and building a pipeline from raw data to prediction results
They work closely with Product Managers, Data Engineers, Backend Engineers, DevOps/Cloud Engineers
open_questions: What are the common data issues AI Engineers face in practice?
Does an AI Engineer need a background in big data?
todos: Further explore academic foundations for AI Engineers (mathematical prerequisites)
Understand how to apply key concepts from linear algebra, statistics, and optimization
